From ca259f6add6f2e5cb01a90052f5257ba09153d07 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: alexfrljuckic <alexfrljuckic@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 23:26:59 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 4/9] feat: Lock-On/Dodge offset port + Span Backgrounds via UI
 Size Setter (2.0)

Two new experimental ultrawide features, both derived from our own
disassembly of the 2.0 exe (master's MIT code as algorithm reference):

- [Span HUD] FixLockOn / FixDodge: port of master's Guard&Lock-On (605904162)
  and Dodge (3550204025) offset formulas, folded into the existing
  UI-Constraints hook (two hooks cannot share one pattern site). 2.0 struct
  offsets: id at +0x1C4, position offsets at +0x1CC/+0x1D0. One-shot
  diagnostics log each element's pre-write state to verify the ids on 2.0.

- [Span Backgrounds]: new "UI Size Setter" hook. Static scan of the exe for
  [reg+0x1BC] readers found the function where every UI element's constraint
  W/H is written ([rax+0x1BC/0x1C0] <- rect W/H, then ret), stamped out at
  three byte-identical sites (exe+0x33437b6/+0x3965bf6/+0x4259049). Overriding
  the registers at the store resizes the element for every downstream
  consumer - upstream of the decoy rect-builder (exe+0x3340ad5) that made the
  register write fire without moving pixels. Logs every 3840x2160 element id
  that passes through (capped) to map menu-bg/combat-overlay candidates.

Infra: Memory::PatternScanAll/FindPatternAll + MAKE_MIDHOOK_ALL to hook every
match of a pattern (needed for the three inlined setter copies).

