Run 1 (2026-07-09, 3440x1440) falsified two assumptions:
- Nothing passes the UI Size Setter at 3840x2160 (menus did not span), and
  dropping the trailing-ret requirement from the pattern reveals the setter
  is inlined at 26 sites with varying register allocation (e.g. exe+0xa7fbfd
  uses xmm4/xmm3), so: hook all 26, after the stores (+0x2A), and write the
  struct fields directly instead of registers.
- Master's Guard/Lock-On and Dodge ids DO exist at +0x1C4 on 2.0, but
  +0x1CC/+0x1D0 hold byte-flags for those elements (0x03/0x33/0x01000101),
  not position floats; the offset writes were useless and are now replaced
  with a one-shot +0x140..+0x220 struct window dump (plus a StaticHUD3840
  baseline dump) to locate the real offset fields.

New: size census logs every unique W/H pair through the setter (units
question: authored 3840x2160 vs HUD pixel space); [Span Backgrounds]
PixelSpace key optionally spans HUD-pixel-sized elements; CreateMidHookAll
logs per-site create_mid failures instead of silently dropping them.

