Run 2 evidence (census + struct dumps) pinned both mechanisms:

- [Span Backgrounds]: full-screen elements never pass the size setter and
  keep W=3840 in the struct, so the rect-builders that draw menu/pause/
  overlay quads never saw the register-only span. Now writes the struct
  constraint width at the UI-Constraints site for 3840x2160 statics
  (+0x1CC == -1), like master's SpanAllHUD did — naturally write-once.
  The size setter hooks remain census-only diagnostics.

- FixLockOn/FixDodge: the real position fields on 2.0 are +0x150/+0x154
  in authored space (guard x=432, dodge x=3008, y=1058.67 — confirmed by
  run-2 dumps); +0x1CC/+0x1D0 are an int index and byte-flags. Shift X by
  -/+(2160*aspect-3840)/2 from a cached original, moving each cluster from
  its 16:9-band position to the true screen edge (matches spanned HUD).

